    <a href="https://speakerdeck.com/arnabdotorg">Slides</a> |
    <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/arnabdotorg/">LinkedIn</a>
  </p>
  <p>How do we help humans work with data better, faster, and more effectively? Arnab's work focuses on bridging human interaction and database systems. He has been recognized by the Association for Computing Machinery as an <a href="https://www.acm.org/media-center/2024/january/distinguished-members-2023">ACM Distinguished Member</a> for his &quot;contributions to human-in-the-loop data infrastructure, next-generation query interfaces, and interactive data analytics systems&quot;. Arnab is a recipient of the US National Science Foundation's CAREER Award, a Google Faculty Research Award, and IEEE's TCDE Early Career Award for his contributions towards user-focused data interaction. Closer to home, Arnab has received the University's Alumni Award for Distinguished Teaching, and the Early Career Innovator of the Year Award. At Ohio State, he co-founded the <a href="https://hack.osu.edu/">OHI/O Program</a>, that fosters a tech culture through hackathons and informal learning, and <a href="https://steamfactory.osu.edu/">The STEAM Factory</a>, an interdisciplinary research and collaboration network. Arnab was founder and CEO of Mobikit, a connected vehicles data analytics startup that was acquired by Azuga Inc., a Bridgestone company. Arnab holds a PhD in Computer Science & Engineering from the University of Michigan.</p>

